Declarer points according to Bergen's method has two parts, 
^c(a). Starting Points and  
^c(b). Additional Points after the fit. 

Therefore, first count the Starting Points then add additional points, according to schedule below-because there is a fit.|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


fp|2|AT|

^Ca. ^dAdd 2 points for a Singleton   |
PG| ***** 7 ***** |


AT| 
^Cb. ^DAdd 4 points for a void        |
PG| ***** 8 ***** |


AT|
^Cc. ^dAdd only 1 point for 2 or 3 Doubletons|
PG| ***** 9 ***** |


AT| 
^Cd. ^dAdd Zero point for one doubleton     |
PG| ***** 10 ***** |


AT| 
^Ce. ^DAdd 1 point for each trump over 5     |
PG| ***** 11 ***** |


AT|
^Cf. ^dAdd 1 point for each and any  4+ side suit.|
