NT||HT|b|cp|4|CS|1|AT|^-{ Bergen Points or Declarer points }
^-|cp||at|^B@2
Let us repeat the schedule as it is outlined in Marty Bergen's book. Declarer Points = a + b
^B-- a. Starting points plus,
^B-- b. Declarer Short Suit After a Raise calculated according to the following guideline.
^C-- A Singleton is a two points assets.
^C-- A Doubleton = 0 point
^C-- 2-3 Doubleton = 1 point only
^C-- A Void = 4 points and not 3 as is traditional
^C-- Add 1 point for each trump over 5
^C-- A 4-card side suit (even a weak one) = 1 point|
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


at|

Please note that a "^*B5-card quality suit ^*N" is particularly valuable in declarer's hand after a fit. Such holding, originally contributes 1 point for length and 1 point for quality to the Starting Points calculation. Then, after the fit declarer adds another point for a 4+ card side suit. Therefore, a 5-card side suit of good quality add 3 points to the value of declarer's hand in addition to its Raw HCP.|
